==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fondly
<hw>Fond"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Foolishly.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark> <rj><au>Verstegan
(1673).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q> Make him speak <qex>fondly</qex> like a frantic man.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In a fond manner; affectionately;
tenderly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q> My heart, untraveled, <qex>fondly</qex> turns to thee.</q>
<rj><qau>Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fondness</ent>⟦br⟧
